svg.text: The theory of cosmic inflation suggests that in the very short time after the Big Bang, the universe will expand for an eternity, stopping only in a small area and forming an infinite number of bubble-like universes. The human visible universe is one of these "bubbles" in the expanding space-time. "The conventional theory of eternal expansion predicts that the universe is an infinite fractal, with different pockets of universes embedded in an ocean of expansion." - Stephen Hawking
